**DOC-08  ·  Revenue ****&**** Monetisation Strategy**

Version 1.0  ·  Confidential  ·  June 2026

# **01  Monetisation philosophy**

***Never paywall before the habit forms. Earn the right to charge.***

The single biggest monetisation mistake a consumer app can make is activating a paywall before users have experienced the product's value enough to miss it. Foofoo's monetisation is sequenced around the habit loop, not around the business need for revenue. The 90-day free period is not generosity — it is the minimum time required for a meal planning habit to form and for the AI to learn the household well enough to be genuinely indispensable.

| **Principle** | **What it means in practice** |
| --- | --- |
| **Habit first, paywall second** | Premium tier is visible from Day 1 but priced ₹0 for 90 days. Users see what they'll eventually pay for. Trust is built before the ask. |
| **Free tier must be genuinely useful** | A free user who sees an ad gets the same quality plan as a premium user. Free is not broken — it's just ad-supported. Users upgrade for convenience and depth, not to access core value. |
| **Every paid feature earns its price** | No feature is behind a paywall simply because we can lock it. Each premium feature must demonstrably improve the user's daily experience enough that the price feels low. |
| **Price anchored to Indian market reality** | ₹99/month is less than one Swiggy order. ₹149/month is less than two. Pricing is framed against the daily behaviour it replaces, not against Western app pricing. |

# **02  Freemium tier design**

## **Three tiers**

| **Feature** | **Free** | **Premium ₹99/mo** | **Premium Plus ₹149/mo** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **Personalised daily meal plan** | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ |
| **Swipe carousel (8 alternatives)** | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ |
| **Never / Not Today / Lock gestures** | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ |
| **Full-text dish search** | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ |
| **Simple ingredient list** | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ |
| **Nutrition summary (basic)** | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ |
| **Morning push notification** | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ |
| **My Meals tab (history)** | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ |
| **Ads between meal cards** | Yes | No | No |
| **Full step-by-step recipes (Phase 0.5)** | Limited (3/week) | Unlimited | Unlimited |
| **Meal insights ****&**** analytics** | ❌ | ✅ | ✅ |
| **Pantry system (Phase 0.5)** | ❌ | ✅ | ✅ |
| **Cooking history ****&**** diary (Phase 1)** | ❌ | ✅ | ✅ |
| **Advanced calorie targeting (Phase 1)** | ❌ | ✅ | ✅ |
| **Grocery list auto-generation (Phase TBD)** | ❌ | ✅ | ✅ |
| **Family profiles (Phase 1.5)** | ❌ | ❌ | ✅ |
| **Health profiles — pregnancy, recovery (Phase 2)** | ❌ | ❌ | ✅ |
| **Member-level analytics** | ❌ | ❌ | ✅ |
| **Priority RE updates (new features first)** | ❌ | ❌ | ✅ |

## **Pricing rationale**

| **₹99/month Premium — the ****'****one Swiggy order****'**** benchmark** The average Swiggy order for a family is ₹300–450. If Foofoo prevents even one impulse Swiggy order per month by having a plan ready, it pays for itself. This is the exact framing used in premium conversion messaging. Not 'save money on food' — 'save the cost of one bad ordering decision.' **₹149/month Premium Plus — the ****'****family planning tool****'**** benchmark** Meera manages 3 meals × 4 family members × 7 days = 84 meal decisions per week. At ₹149/month, Foofoo costs ₹1.78 per meal decision eliminated. Premium Plus is for users who have a complex household (multiple members with different needs) and for whom the time saving is measurable in hours per week, not minutes. |
| --- |

# **03  Revenue model — all streams**

| **Stream** | **Description** | **When active** | **Revenue potential** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **Subscription — Premium ₹99/month** | Ad-free, meal insights, pantry, diary, calorie targeting, grocery list. | Phase 1.5 (Day 90+) | Primary long-term revenue driver |
| **Subscription — Premium Plus ₹149/month** | Everything in Premium + family profiles, health profiles, member analytics. | Phase 1.5 (Day 90+) | Higher ARPU for complex households |
| **In-app advertising** | Banner ads between meal cards for free users. Contextual food-adjacent categories (grocery, kitchenware, healthy snacks). | Phase 1.5 (concurrent with premium) | Secondary. Monetises free users. |
| **Affiliate — grocery delivery** | Commission on orders placed via Blinkit/Zepto from Foofoo grocery list. | Phase 3 | 3–5% commission per order |
| **Affiliate — food delivery** | Commission on Zomato/Swiggy orders placed via Foofoo 'Order Instead' CTA. | Phase 3 | 1–2% commission per order |
| **B2B — corporate wellness** | Meal planning for corporate canteens or employee wellness programmes. | Year 2 | Different sales motion — out of consumer scope |

# **04  Financial projections — 3-year model**

Projections are conservative estimates based on organic-only growth through Phase 1 and modest paid marketing in Phase 1.5+. All figures in INR.

## **Year 1 — validation and habit formation**

| **Month** | **DAU** | **MAU** | **Paying users** | **MRR** | **Notes** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **Month 1–3 (MVP)** | 50→500 | 500→3,000 | 0 | ₹0 | Free period. All users on free tier. |
| **Month 4 (Phase 0.5)** | 500→1,000 | 3,000→8,000 | 0 | ₹0 | Free period continues. |
| **Month 5–6 (Phase 1)** | 1,000→2,000 | 8,000→18,000 | 0 | ₹0 | Free period. Premium visible at ₹0. |
| **Month 7 (Phase 1.5 — paywall activates)** | 2,000→3,000 | 18,000→30,000 | 600–900 (3%) | ₹60,000–90,000 | First revenue. Referral drives conversion. |
| **Month 8** | 3,000→4,000 | 30,000→45,000 | 900–1,800 | ₹90,000–1,80,000 | Paid marketing begins (small). |
| **Month 9–12** | 4,000→8,000 | 45,000→100,000 | 1,800–4,000 | ₹1,80,000–4,00,000 | Scale begins if metrics hold. |

