# **06  Premium conversion strategy**

## **The conversion funnel**

| **Stage** | **Trigger** | **Mechanic** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **Free trial (Day 0–90)** | Automatic — all users start here | No paywall. Full value visible. Premium badge on locked features. |
| **Awareness (Day 14–60)** | User sees premium features labelled in UI | Meal insights tab shows 'Premium' label. Family profile shows 'Premium Plus'. No prompt yet. |
| **Intent signal (Day 60–90)** | User taps a Premium feature | First prompt: 'This is a Premium feature. You have [N] days of free access remaining. Upgrade anytime.' |
| **Conversion prompt (Day 85–90)** | Free period ending soon | In-app notification 7 days before: 'Your free Premium period ends in 7 days. Keep your ad-free plan for ₹99/month.' |
| **Conversion (Day 90)** | Free period ends | Single clear screen: Free vs Premium vs Premium Plus. UPI autopay. 1-tap activation. |
| **Retention (Day 90+)** | Ongoing | Premium users see no ads. Premium Plus users get family analytics. Referral rewards stack. |

## **Conversion messaging at Day 90**

| **For Meera (Premium Plus target):** *'**Your family**'**s plan has been running for 90 days. Foofoo now knows [member names], your home state preferences, and [N] dishes your family loves. Keep all of this — and unlock family analytics, member profiles, and the full grocery list — for ₹149/month.**'* **For Riya (Premium target):** *'**You**'**ve saved [N] Swiggy decisions this month. Keep Foofoo ad-free and unlock meal insights for ₹99/month — less than one order.**'* |
| --- |

